## 4. Functional Requirements

### FR-UI-1: Login Page
The system shall provide a login page with username and password fields.  
On successful authentication, the JWT token shall be stored in `localStorage` and the user shall be redirected to the Query page.  
On failure, a visible error message shall be displayed.

### FR-UI-2: Protected Routes
All pages except the login page shall require a valid JWT token.  
If the token is missing or expired, the user shall be redirected to the login page automatically.

### FR-UI-3: Query Interface
The system shall provide a text input field for natural language queries.  
The user shall be able to configure `top_k` (range: 1–10, default: 3) via a slider or input.  
On submission, the frontend shall call `POST /query` with Bearer token authentication.

### FR-UI-4: Answer Display
The generated answer shall be rendered in a readable text area.  
LaTeX expressions (`\( \)`, `\[ \]`) within the answer shall be rendered using a math rendering library (e.g., KaTeX).

### FR-UI-5: Citation Viewer
Each citation returned in the response shall be displayed as an expandable card showing:
- `source_filename`
- `section_header`
- `page_number`
- `score` (displayed as a percentage or progress bar)

### FR-UI-6: Status and Warnings Display
The response `status` field (`ok` / `partial`) shall be visually indicated.  
Any `warnings` strings shall be displayed below the answer in a distinct color (e.g., amber).

### FR-UI-7: Loading State
While awaiting a response from the backend, the UI shall display a loading indicator.  
The query submit button shall be disabled during the pending state to prevent duplicate requests.

### FR-UI-8: Document Upload (Lab PI+ only)
Users with Lab PI or Admin role shall see an Upload page accessible via navigation.  
The page shall provide a file input accepting `.pdf`, `.md`, `.txt` files.  
On upload, the frontend shall call `POST /ingest` with the file as `multipart/form-data`.  
The result (chunks indexed, filename) shall be displayed upon completion.

### FR-UI-9: Health Indicator
The navigation bar shall display a backend health status badge.  
The frontend shall call `GET /health` on page load and reflect the result (online / offline).

### FR-UI-10: Logout
The user shall be able to log out from the navigation bar.  
Logout shall clear the JWT from `localStorage` and redirect to the login page.

