## 5. Non-Functional Requirements

### NFR-UI-1: Offline Compatibility
The Web UI shall function without any external CDN or web font requests in production build mode.  
All dependencies shall be bundled locally via Vite.

### NFR-UI-2: Response Rendering Latency
The UI shall render the backend response within 100ms of receiving it, excluding network latency.

### NFR-UI-3: Token Security
The JWT token shall be stored in `localStorage`.  
The token shall never be logged to the browser console or exposed in URL parameters.

### NFR-UI-4: Error Visibility
All API errors (4xx, 5xx) shall surface a human-readable message in the UI.  
Raw stack traces or internal error details shall not be displayed to end users.

### NFR-UI-5: Extensibility
Component structure shall be organized to allow addition of Admin and document management pages in v2.1.0 without refactoring existing components.

